OL,6,FCommenting on the delay to Torbay,
OL,7,FSouth Devon's Liberal Democrat MP,
OL,8,FCaroline Voaden, said: "For years,
OL,9,FTorbay Hospital was repeatedly let
OL,10,Fdown by the Conservatives, and Labour
OL,11,Fare picking up where they left off.
OL,13,F"For the government to delay repairs
OL,14,Fto a hospital whose estate is nearly
OL,15,Fentirely unfit for purpose is
OL,16,Funforgivable. This decision must
OL,17,Furgently be reviewed; it's
OL,18,Funacceptable that in 2024, patients
OL,19,Fare being treated in a hospital with a
OL,20,Fleaking roof, crumbling concrete and
OL,21,Fsewage running down the corridor."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/13
